      <h2 class="lowerh2">Demonstration of the DICOM Modality Worklist Service</h2>
      <p>In 1996, the DICOM standard was extended by the new "Modality Worklist Service" which enables a modality to directly download a worklist together with demographic patient data from an information system. Through this new service, a manual input of patient data at a modality's console - which had frequently proven to be a reason for data inconsistencies in an archive - was made unnecessary. In accordance with this new service, OFFIS developed the "Modality Worklist CTN" application, an enhancement of the <a class="textlink" href="dcmtk.php.en">OFFIS DICOM Toolkit</a>. This application was the world's first server implementation of the Modality Worklist Service and it was demonstrated at the following congresses:</p>
